Given	I'm logged-in with valid credentials
And	I'm on Page 04 - Bones of Shoulder MRI
And I select the radio button 'Finding'
And I select 'Bone marrow edema' from the Finding dropdown
An I select 'Scapula' checkbox
Then 'Akromion' checkbox is enabled
And 'Processus coracoideus' checkbox is enabled
And 'Scapular spine' checkbox is enabled
And 'Supraspinatous fossa' checkbox is enabled
And 'Glenoid fossa' checkbox is enabled
And 'Infraspinatous fossa' checkbox is enabled


And 'Subchondral' radio button is enabled
And 'Focal' radio button is enabled
And 'Diffuse' radio button is enabled
And 'Diffuse-patchy' radio button is enabled
And 'Subcortical edema formation (fine subchondral lines)' radio button is enabled
And 'Soft tissue edema' checkbox is enabled
And 'Thickened and edematized synovialis' checkbox is enabled
